Wind and Water

The lily,
  and the dark stem
from the water,
linked by still-enfolding
  waves, by fingers of the
    stream that moves.

The deep rose,
  the roar of forests,
lost in the twist
of darkness—

the root in me, the sea woven,
  the gray longing
  to call from the south.

H.D.

- HD
